Durban - The getaway car that four armed robbers used in the uMhlanga jewellery shop robbery last week had been hijacked from a residential neighbourhood just outside the city.
Durban North SAPS spokesperson Captain Raymond Deokaran said the Hyundai Elantra was recovered on Portland Drive, a few kilometres from Protea Mall on Chartwell Drive, where Anastasia Jewellers was robbed on Thursday.
“The getaway vehicle was recovered about 5km from where the incident took place. When we searched the vehicle we found out that it had been hijacked in Cato Manor,” said Deokaran.
Gregory Munemo, a witness, said the robbers took about two minutes inside the shop before two men came out with bags; two more were waiting in the getaway car.


 






